The '''A4230''' is a suburban main road in south [[Wales]].

The A4230 is a single carriageway road for its whole length.  It begins at the Peniel Green roundabout (junction with the [[M4 motorway]] and the [[A48 road|A48]]) in the far east of [[Llansamlet]].  It travels east through the Lonlas area of Skewen before passing through central [[Skewen]], after which it traverses the Neath Abbey area before connecting with the [[A474 road|A474]] at the Cwrt Herbert roundabout in [[Dyffryn Clydach]].  It then follows the same road as the [[A474]] along Neath Abbey Road then though [[Cadoxton-juxta-Neath|Cadoxton]] until it connects with the [[A465 road|A465]] just south of [[Aberdulais]].

