{{Galaxy cluster | name = [[Abell catalogue|Abell]] 2162 | image = | epoch = [[Epoch (astronomy)#Julian years and J2000|J2000]] | constellation = [[Corona Borealis]] | ra = {{RA|16|12|30.0}} | dec = {{DEC|+29|32|23}} | member_no = | brightest_member = | richness = | bmtype = I | velocity_dispersion = | redshift = | distance = | temperature = | mass = | luminosity = | flux = | other_names = }}
'''Abell 2162''' is a [[galaxy cluster]] in the [[Abell catalogue]] located in the constellation [[Corona Borealis]]. It is a member of the [[Hercules Superclusters]],<ref>{{cite journal|author=Einasto, M.|author2=Einasto, J.|author3=Tago, E.|author4=Müller, V.|author5=Andernach, H.|date=2001|title=Optical and X-Ray Clusters as Tracers of the Supercluster-Void Network. I. Superclusters of Abell and X-Ray Clusters|journal=The Astronomical Journal|volume=122|issue=5|pages=2222–2242| doi=10.1086/323707| bibcode=2001AJ....122.2222E|arxiv = astro-ph/0012536 }}</ref> the redshifts of the member galaxies of which lie between 0.0304 and 0.0414. The cluster hosts a massive [[Type-cD galaxy]] called [[NGC 6086]]. <ref>{{cite journal|author=Kopylova, F. G.|author2=Kopylov, A. I.|date=2013|title=Investigation of properties of galaxy clusters in the Hercules supercluster region|journal=Astronomy Letters|volume=39|issue=1|pages=1–16|doi=10.1134/S1063773712120043 | bibcode= 2013AstL...39....1K }}</ref>
