{{Infobox museum | name = Cape Town Science Centre | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Cape Town Science Centre.jpg | image_upright = | caption = Cape Town Science Centre, Main Rd, Observatory | alt = Cape Town Science Centre, Main Rd, Observatory | map_type = Cape Town | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | map_dot_label = | coordinates = {{coord|-33.9383|18.4640|region:ZA|display=inline,title}} | established = {{Start date|2011|12|28|df=y}} | dissolved = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | location = [[Observatory, Cape Town]] | type = [[Science museum]] | accreditation = | key_holdings = | collections = | collection_size = | visitors = | founder = | director = Julie Cleverdon | president = | curator = | owner = | publictransit = | car_park = | parking = | network = | website = {{URL|http://ctsc.org.za/}} }}
The '''Cape Town Science Centre''' is a not-for-profit<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saastec.co.za/news/nstfawards2002.html |title=National Science and Technology Foundation Awards for 2002 |date=2002-05-13 |work=saastec.co.za |publisher=South African Association of Science and Technology Centres |accessdate=2009-01-06 |archivedate=2009-01-06 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5ddJwePi5?url=http://www.saastec.co.za/news/nstfawards2002.html |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> [[science centre]] in [[Cape Town]], [[South Africa]]. It forms part of a wide range of non-classroom initiatives to improve the quality of science understanding and [[scientific literacy|science literacy]] in South Africa.
Until early 2010, the MTN Sciencentre was located in the [[Canal Walk]] shopping mall.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.capeargus.co.za/index.php?fSectionId=&fArticleId=4088381|title=The power of the city lies in science|date=2007-10-22|work=Cape Argus|accessdate=2009-01-06|archivedate=2009-01-06|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5ddJIQVBp?url=http://www.capeargus.co.za/index.php?fSectionId=&fArticleId=4088381|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> It will reopen in [[Observatory, Cape Town|Observatory]] later in 2011.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news24.com/SciTech/News/New-home-for-Cape-science-centre-20101102|title=New home for Cape science centre|date=2010-11-02|publisher=News24}}</ref>
The MTN Sciencentre's [[Ericsson]] [[cell phone]] is in the [[Guinness Book of World Records]] as the world's largest working cell phone.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.biz-community.com/Snippet/196/78/8226.html |title=Officially the world's largest cellphone |work=BIZCommunity.com |accessdate=2009-01-06 |archivedate=2009-01-06 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5ddJcCR7J?url=http://www.biz-community.com/Snippet/196/78/8226.html |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
