{{Taxobox | color = violet | name = ''Ectromelia virus'' | virus_group = i | ordo = ''Unassigned'' | familia = ''[[Poxviridae]]'' | subfamilia = ''[[Chordopoxvirinae]]'' | genus = ''[[Orthopoxvirus]]'' | type_species = ''[[Vaccinia virus]]'' | subdivision_ranks = Species | subdivision = '''''Ectromelia virus''''' }} '''Ectromelia virus''' (ECTV) is a [[virus]] of the family ''[[Poxviridae]]'' and the genus ''[[Orthopoxvirus]]'' that causes '''mousepox''', a disease of [[mouse|mice]]. It has only been seen in mouse colonies kept for research purposes.<ref name=Fenner_1993>{{cite book|author1=Fenner, Frank J. |author2=Gibbs, E. Paul J. |author3=Murphy, Frederick A. |author4=Rott, Rudolph |author5=Studdert, Michael J. |author6=White, David O. |title=Veterinary Virology (2nd ed.)|publisher=Academic Press, Inc|year=1993|isbn=978-0-12-253056-2}}</ref> Mousepox causes skin lesions and generalized disease, which can be fatal. It is the only poxvirus to cause disease naturally in mice.
