In [[infrared astronomy]], the '''H band''' refers to an [[infrared window|atmospheric transmission window]] centred on 1.65 micrometres with a [[Full width at half maximum]] of 0.35 [[micrometres]]<ref name="McClean">Ian McClean, Electronic Imaging in Astronomy, Second Edition, Springer, 2008.</ref>
(in the [[near-infrared]]).

