There are 428 named lakes in [[Oneida County, Wisconsin]], along with 701 with no names. Together they make up 68,447 acres of surface area. [[Willow Flowage]], at 6,306 acres, is the largest. Oneida County is the county with the second largest number of lakes in Wisconsin, after neighboring [[Vilas County, Wisconsin|Vilas County]].<ref name="dnr">Wisconsin Dept. of Natural Resources, ''[http://dnr.wi.gov/lakes/lakebook/wilakes2009bma.pdf Wisconsin Lakes]''. 2009.</ref>
